Sorry to both of you, the beginning of the year has been a bit more chaotic than expected but I should have more time rather soon.

Nitpick:
```suggestion
    induced (â‹ƒâ‚€ ð”–).restrict (Pi.topologicalSpace (Y := fun i : (â‹ƒâ‚€ ð”–) â†¦ Ï€ i)) =
```

```suggestion
    UniformSpace.comap (â‹ƒâ‚€ ð”–).restrict (Pi.uniformSpace (fun i : (â‹ƒâ‚€ ð”–) â†¦ Î± i)) =
```

```suggestion
instance [Subsingleton Î²] : Subsingleton (Î± â†’áµ¤ Î²) :=
```

```suggestion
instance [Subsingleton Î²] : Subsingleton (Î± â†’áµ¤[ð”–] Î²) :=
```
This change looks unnecessary. I'm guessing this is a legacy of merging master. Shouldn't we just leave this alone?
Indeed, I think this is what happened. Reverted.

This comment is fine (and actually is consistent with the rest of the comments in this file) but it really just repeats the contents of the Lean.

IMHO, we underuse comments as an opportunity to express the mathematical content in more conventional informal mathematical terminology.

I agree with you to some extent, although working with beginners at LFTCM made me remember that it takes some work to be able to *read* Lean statements. I'll admit that sometimes I do so just because it takes more energy to write down the full statement without referencing the Lean objects at play.

In this particular case though, I think it looks useless in the source but not so much in the generated documentation because of the lack of type ascriptions. For example you can look at the similar [UniformOnFun.uniformContinuous_restrict](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/UniformSpace/UniformConvergenceTopology.html#UniformOnFun.uniformContinuous_restrict), where the docstring improves readability just by making the types explicit.
Although now that I say that, the statement I linked to doesn't write down the Lean term for the restriction map. Should I do the same here?
I did that for now, let me know what you think.
What you've got is great, I don't think we need to hold up this really useful PR any more by my quibbles.
If we're doing this, then how about the same change just above on line 25?

```suggestion
  is strictly weaker.
```
Could you clarify what you mean by "this" here: I presume you mean establishing the intermediate total boundedness result a la Bourbaki?
Don't you want me to change this before merging? I was planning to do it tomorrow morning. I can also change the wording later if you want.

I decided I was splitting hairs and it wasn't worth delaying this PR any further.

Feel free to follow up with a doc string adjustment PR or not, according to your taste!

```suggestion
open Set Filter Uniformity Topology Function UniformConvergence
```

```suggestion
variable {Î¹ X Y Î± Î² : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [UniformSpace Î±] [UniformSpace Î²]
```
